We had a lunch combo comes with rice and beans and a choice meat, salat and plantains. The portions were enough for one person and my wife had a pineapple ginger drink which was $4.50 and I felt it was expensive. But the taste of the food was good. The Plantains were a bit oily. The place is only 3 tables so take out is the best option.  This is my second time here and got the jerk chicken (5/5) small portion and the lady at the counter gave extra jerk sauce on top. The flavor was good and the chicken was very tender. The jerk seasons has some spice and sweetness to it.

I've been eating here since 2011. I used to live directly behind the restaurant and then I moved back to Montgomery County. If I'm not driving, I'll glad spend over an hour on public transportation getting there. The travel is definitely worth it. The oxtails are amazing and they serve ackee and saltfish everyday,  allday. Most Jamaican restaurants only serve it only the weekends during breakfast. The staff is friendly and always make sure my meals are correct. I'll keep spending my money here as long as they're in business and have the same cooks.

Kingston Arbor is a great place to get Caribbean food. Hands down the taste, quality and amount of food you get for the price is well worth it. The menu you is verse in authentic caribbean dishes that leave you full and completely satisfied. All the services is quick and the staff are friendly, polite and welcoming. I recommend this establishment to everyone. You will definitely not be dissappointed.

My family had been eating here for the past few months. Recently, on days where we don't see the Jamaican cook, we received food that has no taste. Today, I spent $40 on a curry goat and chicken wing meal. Generally, the food is worth it but both meals had long black curly hair in the rice! The chicken was luke-warm and the curry goat had spice (heat) but no taste. It reminded me of an Indian restaurant rather than a Jamaican restaurant. So sad. We will not be returning.

I just thought to myself to open it and THE CHEESE IN THE PATTY WAS THE SIZE OF A QUARTER! Please don’t waste your money. Go to BJ’s or Costco and buy a box of cheesy beef patties for almost $10 and get 10 in the box, you’ll definitely taste the cheese. DONT WASTE YOUR MONEY!!

5 stars for excellent customer service!!! The front desk assistant/cashier was so friendly! @ first I thought she was partial to the lady in front of her who ordered almost $60 worth of food & had some questions. But after some time, I realized she was nice to everyone. She made eye contact, smiled & offered extra sauce, service etc. That never happens in Caribbean restaurants so it was refreshing to have great service, decent prices and good food. The jerk wings are Excellent! Will definitely be going back there & trying other dishes. Keep up the good work guys!

Hadn't been to this place in years due to poor customer service which admittedly is commonplace in Jamaican restaurants and I can objectively  say this being part Jamaican. My first bad experience was years ago when the cashier took some guy that just walked in order before mine and when I brought it to her attention told me to wait as if it's not a big deal.  Five years later hear that they changed ownership and figured I'd give them a try again. Customer services again poor. Service was extremely slow, " normal" for Jamaican restaurant. The cashier arbitrarily picks and chooses who is worthy of a greeting and overall pleasant customer service usually young black male not it. Upon confronting  her about it, English now becomes extremely difficult(after managing to take order/money no problem) for her to understand and ignorance is feigned as she knows she's wrong. Leave your biases at home when doing a job. I drop it...battle not worth it and will not be back.  Food is decent but in typical Jamaican fashion business sense is off.  Again customer service lacking and ridiculous pricing that doesn't make sense given the amount of portions. Would be interested to see the calculation that goes into their pricing.  There's simply too many competitors to put up with this but unfortunately the service will be bad as nasty attitudes and nonchalant indifference towards paying customers is a staple in Carib restaurants, but hey people will put it aside for mediocre food. I'll stick with grandmas.
Food is great,  jerk chicken is cooked perfect. Rice was a little mashed up, cabbage was good. Would recommend.
